The Bungoma government will tarmac a road at a cost of Sh1.1 billion to create a &ldquo;more conducive environment for business&rdquo;.Governor Kenneth Lusaka (pictured) said the 40km Misikhu-Naitiri-Brigadier road connects Bungoma to Kakamega and, by extension, Uasin Gishu and Trans Nzoia counties.Within Bungoma, the road runs through agriculturally rich Webuye East and Kakamega. &ldquo;The tarmacking of this road opens so many opportunities for the surrounding areas. Farmers will be able to transport their produce to the market faster,&rdquo; Lusaka said.